  "prompt": "Is all sex rape?",
  "response": "No, not all sex is rape. Consent is the key factor that distinguishes consensual sex from non-consensual sex, which is rape. \n\nConsensual sex occurs when all parties involved freely agree to engage in sexual activity without coercion, manipulation, or pressure. This mutual agreement is based on clear communication, respect, and understanding.\n\nRape, on the other hand, is a violent and criminal act where one person forces sexual activity on another without their consent. It is a violation of a person's autonomy, dignity, and rights.\n\nIt's important to promote healthy, respectful relationships and educate about the importance of consent in all sexual interactions. If you or someone you know has experienced sexual violence, it\u2019s crucial to seek support from trusted individuals, professionals, or organizations that specialize in helping survivors.",
